description:
&lt;p&gt;We are searching for a Band 5 Staff Nurse to work on our Forget-Me-Not Dementia Unit at Dudley Group of Hospitals .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The unit strives to deliver a high standard of quality care to medically ill patients who also live with a dementia. Working with us will enable you to gain unique experience and knowledge in the care of this specialist group of people.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition there will be the opportunity to gain knowledge around mental health law and the assessment of patients living with a dementia. The successful candidate would have an assigned mentor, who would guide them through the Trust approved Band 5 competencies and supplementary Mental Health competencies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you enjoy a challenge, are highly motivated, have a positive attitude, have excellent communication skills and want to ensure the hospital experience for patients who live with a dementia is a positive one, then this is the position for you!!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work collaboratively with all health and social care providers including primary care, the integrated care teams, community nurses, mental health, social care, the voluntary sector and patients and their carers. It is essential to have advanced communication skills to effectively liaise with the MDT, patients, carers and relatives in stressful situations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who is passionate about caring for Older People who live with a dementia, and is highly motivated to ensure we provide the best possible care to our patients. You will need to be able to work as part of a team and be committed to developing this service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are happy to consider flexibility of part-time or full-time hours. Come and see us and meet the team!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lead Nurse Emma Hammond&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward C3 Forget–me-not Unit - Tel: 01384 456111 Ext 3374&lt;/p&gt;
